    "title": {
      "rendered": "10 Online Fundraising Best Practices for Nonprofits"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-16597\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"Online Fundraising Best Practices Square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Online-Fundraising-Best-Practices-Square.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>In 2013 online giving grew 13.5% according to the <a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/nonprofit-resources/charitablegiving-infographic\">Blackbaud</a><a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/nonprofit-resources/charitablegiving-infographic\"> Index of Online Giving</a> and 14% according to the <a href=\"http://www1.networkforgood.org/digitalgivingindex\">Network for Good\u2019s Online Giving Index</a>\u00a0with small and medium-sized nonprofits are experiencing the largest growth. In addition,\u00a0charitable giving is at an <a href=\"http://www.salsalabs.com/support-community/blog/new-report-shows-charitable-giving-record-high\">all-time high</a> in the United States and nonprofits would be wise to invest in upgrades to their online donation service to ensure that they are meeting the needs of today&#8217;s online donors. &#8220;Donate Now&#8221; buttons were launched in the late 1990&#8217;s and since then the nonprofit sector has learned through trial and error the basics of successful online fundraising:</p>\n<h2>1. Embed the donation process inside your website and ensure that it is mobile compatible.</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www1.networkforgood.org/digitalgivingindex\">Six times more money\u00a0is raised</a> through custom-branded donate pages than through third-party donate\u00a0pages. To successfully fundraise online, nonprofits must invest in a premium, mobile-compatible online fundraising service, such as <a href=\"http://www1.networkforgood.org/\">Network for Good</a>, <a href=\"https://www.stayclassy.org/\">StayClassy</a>, <a href=\"https://www.givlet.org/\">Givlet</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.donationpay.org/site/\">DonationPay</a>, since\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2014/06/08/14-must-know-stats-about-fundraising-social-media-and-mobile-technology/\">responsive design doubles giving</a> on mobile devices.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/corps-nonprofits.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16550\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/corps-nonprofits.jpg?resize=600%2C489\" alt=\"corps nonprofits\" width=\"600\" height=\"489\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/corps-nonprofits.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/corps-nonprofits.jpg?resize=300%2C244&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.mercycorps.org/donate\">mercycorps.org/donate</a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/mercy-mobile.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-16575 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/mercy-mobile.jpg?resize=450%2C675\" alt=\"mercy mobile\" width=\"450\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/mercy-mobile.jpg?w=450&amp;ssl=1 450w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/mercy-mobile.jpg?resize=200%2C300&amp;ssl=1 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.mercycorps.org/donate\">mercycorps.org/donate</a></strong></p>\n<h2>2. Prominently feature a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button on every page of your website.</h2>\n<p>Add a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button to every page of your website and blog which is mostly easily done by integrating\u00a0it into your site&#8217;s navigation. The color of the button should be bold to ensure that donors can immediately see and tap or click the button.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.conservation.org/Pages/default.aspx\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16537\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Conservation-Internation-Donate-Button.png?resize=600%2C266\" alt=\"Conservation Internation Donate Button\" width=\"600\" height=\"266\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Conservation-Internation-Donate-Button.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Conservation-Internation-Donate-Button.png?resize=300%2C133&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>conservation.org</strong></a></p>\n<h2>3. Add calls-to-action to your &#8220;Thank You&#8221; landing page.</h2>\n<p>The vast majority of \u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2014/07/06/6-fresh-ideas-for-your-nonprofits-thank-you-landing-page/\">&#8220;Thank You&#8221; landing pages</a> are text-only and lacking in interesting content. Add visual calls-to-actions to better motivate your donors to take further action on behalf of your nonprofit.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/WWF-Thank-You-Landing-Page-3.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16427\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/WWF-Thank-You-Landing-Page-3.png?resize=600%2C335\" alt=\"WWF Thank You Landing Page 3\" width=\"600\" height=\"335\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/WWF-Thank-You-Landing-Page-3.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/WWF-Thank-You-Landing-Page-3.png?resize=300%2C167&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>\u00a04. Create donation impact graphics for social media.</h2>\n<p>Your followers on social networks are much more likely to take notice of your fundraising asks if you create a series of donation impact graphics. The ideal size for Facebook/Pinterest/Google+ graphics is 500 x 500 pixels. The size necessary for Twitter is 500 x 250 pixels.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/OXFAM.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16585\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/OXFAM.png?resize=502%2C516\" alt=\"OXFAM\" width=\"502\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/OXFAM.png?w=502&amp;ssl=1 502w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/OXFAM.png?resize=291%2C300&amp;ssl=1 291w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>5. Have a &#8220;More Ways to Give&#8221; page.</h2>\n<p>&#8220;Donate&#8221; buttons should always link directly to a page where donors enter their credit card information, but in addition your nonprofit should have a &#8220;More Ways to Give&#8221; or &#8220;How to Help&#8221; page the lists all the ways supporters can donate to your nonprofit. Again, prioritize images of text.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/nature-conservancy.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16586\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/nature-conservancy.png?resize=600%2C403\" alt=\"nature conservancy\" width=\"600\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/nature-conservancy.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/nature-conservancy.png?resize=300%2C201&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>nature.org/membership-giving/more-ways-to-give</strong></a></p>\n<h2>6. Launch a sustainer program.</h2>\n<p>Use an online fundraising service that easily allows supporters to make monthly donations automatically.\u00a0Monthly donors give an <a href=\"http://www.nonprofitmarketingblog.com/comments/new_infographic_why_recurring_giving_matters\">average monthly gift of $52 ($624 annually)</a> and give 42% more over one-year than one-time donors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/conservation-international.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16588\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/conservation-international.png?resize=600%2C310\" alt=\"conservation international\" width=\"600\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/conservation-international.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/conservation-international.png?resize=300%2C155&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>conservation.org/donate</strong></a></p>\n<h2>7. Enable tribute giving.</h2>\n<p>Use an online fundraising service that easily allows\u00a0donors to make tribute or honor gifts, such birthday, holiday, and wedding gifts.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16590\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/oceana.png?resize=600%2C391\" alt=\"oceana\" width=\"600\" height=\"391\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/oceana.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/oceana.png?resize=300%2C195&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/oceana.png\">oceana.org/donate</a></strong></p>\n<h2>8. Prioritize year-end fundraising.</h2>\n<p>Thirty percent of all online donations are made in December and 10% of all annual giving happens in the last three days of the year. Online fundraising campaigns should be focused on the online giving habits of their donors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ten-percent-of-all-giving.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16223\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ten-percent-of-all-giving.png?resize=600%2C441\" alt=\"ten percent of all giving\" width=\"600\" height=\"441\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ten-percent-of-all-giving.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ten-percent-of-all-giving.png?resize=300%2C220&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>networkforgood.org/digitalgivingindex</strong></a></p>\n<h2>9.\u00a0Advertise\u00a0your fundraising campaigns on your blog.</h2>\n<p>In a addition to a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button on every page of your blog, create ads for other fundraising programs, such as products your nonprofit sells, apps you have available for download, crowdfunding campaigns, monthly giving campaigns, etc.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.aspca.org/blog\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16533\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ASPCA-Blog.png?resize=600%2C350\" alt=\"ASPCA Blog\" width=\"600\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ASPCA-Blog.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ASPCA-Blog.png?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>aspca.org/blog</strong></a></p>\n<h2>10. Publish an e-newsletter.</h2>\n<p>When polled, 25-30% of nonprofits do not use email to promote their programs and fundraising campaigns which is a mistake since email is the primary source of online donations. In fact, for every 1,000 fundraising messages delivered, <a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\">nonprofits raised $17</a>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.splcenter.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16532\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/SPLC-Email-Newsletter.png?resize=600%2C467\" alt=\"SPLC Email Newsletter\" width=\"600\" height=\"467\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/SPLC-Email-Newsletter.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/SPLC-Email-Newsletter.png?resize=300%2C233&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>splcenter.org/stay-informed</strong><br />\n</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
